replies.bodyText:
The old code (the line I've commented on here) did:
response.setStatusCode(statusCode).end(buffer);

whereas the new code does:
routingContext.fail(statusCode, exception);

The latter doesn't populate the response status code and message (buffer), right? As a result, failed curl requests come up blank. I remember being really confused by this when doing manual testing.

